            h2 General info
            p
              | Tiles are the representation of your app or sub module. The content shown on your tile can, and ideally should, change regularly, especially if your tile can communicate new, real-time information to your user. Tiles can show a combination of text and images, and a badge to show status.
              | Tile is a block object and can be placed in any container.
            p
              | The default tile size is 150x150 pixels. Tile size may be increased with add the next subclasses for tile object:
              code .double(-vertical)
              | ,
              code .triple(-vertical)
              | ,
              code .quadro(-vertical)
              | .
            p
              | For tile may be set status "selected". You also may be change background color for tile with classes
              code .bg-color-*
            h3 Tile definition:
            pre.prettyprint.linenums.
              \n    <div class="tile"></div>
                  <div class="tile double"></div>
                  <div class="tile selected"></div>
                  <div class="tile bg-color-orange"></div>

            .clearfix
              .tile
              .tile.double
              .tile.selected
              .tile.bg-color-orange
            h3 Tile content
            p
              | Tile content can be placed in sub container with class
              code .tile-content
              | . Class .tile-content has padding 10px from top, bottom and 15px from left, right.
            pre.prettyprint.linenums.
              \n    <div class="tile">
                      <div class="tile-content">

                      </div>
                  </div>

            .clearfix
